## Decisions Made
- Re-stat the events file after `appendEvent` instead of computing `size + bytesWritten`: `appendEvent` does not return the byte count, and re-stat is robust to concurrent writers (state-commit, other monitors). The cost is one extra `fs.statSync` per change-tick, which is negligible at the ~15s interval.
- On stat failure, fall back to the pre-append `size` rather than `lastEventSize` so we do not re-emit the same event on the next tick.

## Problems Encountered
- CodeRabbit suggested either "add bytes written" or "re-stat after append". The first option would require changing `appendEvent`'s return signature, rippling through five other call sites. Resolved by choosing re-stat, which is local to `eventTail()`.

## Constraints Identified
- `appendEvent` is fire-and-forget (`fs.appendFileSync` with no return value); changing it would touch all five monitor functions. The local fix in `eventTail` is the minimal, contained change.
- The monitor runs at `intervalMs >= 1000ms`; the extra `statSync` per change-tick is well below the budget.

